00:35:13.850 --> 00:35:16.410
Thank you.

00:35:16.410 --> 00:35:19.990
I thought of all the
possible crimes, many of them

00:35:19.990 --> 00:35:22.170
violent, that would
lead to a girl

00:35:22.170 --> 00:35:25.120
to be locked up in this
place, and her circumstances,

00:35:25.120 --> 00:35:29.240
and what privileges
she didn't have,

00:35:29.240 --> 00:35:32.600
or what would lead
her to be left here.

00:35:32.600 --> 00:35:35.160
And so many of the
girls, it's like they are

00:35:35.160 --> 00:35:36.990
considered to have no future.

00:35:36.990 --> 00:35:38.860
And even if their
sentences end, what

00:35:38.860 --> 00:35:42.500
happens to them after, when
you've spent all this time

00:35:42.500 --> 00:35:44.180
incarcerated in this place?

00:35:44.180 --> 00:35:47.970
And so I thought of all
the possible crimes.

00:35:47.970 --> 00:35:51.640
And then I thought of the girl
who might have committed this

00:35:51.640 --> 00:35:55.057
crime or was accused
of it and didn't.

00:35:55.057 --> 00:35:56.640
There's a point in
here where it says,

00:35:56.640 --> 00:35:58.147
they all say they're innocent.

00:35:58.147 --> 00:35:59.230
Some of them are innocent.

00:35:59.230 --> 00:36:01.270
Some of them aren't innocent.

00:36:01.270 --> 00:36:05.790
And so it was fun and
interesting to create

00:36:05.790 --> 00:36:08.610
these girls who had had
these terrible mistakes

00:36:08.610 --> 00:36:10.190
and ended up here.

00:36:10.190 --> 00:36:13.150
And there are quite
a few of them.

00:36:13.150 --> 00:36:15.550
And I feel like I could
have gone and written

00:36:15.550 --> 00:36:20.450
whole sections, whole chapters
about them and their stories.

00:36:20.450 --> 00:36:23.354
I could've kept going.

